'''''Meu Pé de Laranja Lima''''' (''My Sweet Orange Tree'') is a 1970 Brazilian [[drama film]], based on the [[Meu Pé de Laranja Lima|novel of the same name]]. Directed by [[Aurélio Teixeira]], is the first film adaptation of the novel by [[José Mauro de Vasconcelos]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cinemateca.gov.br/cgi-bin/wxis.exe/iah/?IsisScript=iah/iah.xis&base=FILMOGRAFIA&lang=p&nextAction=lnk&exprSearch=ID=014599&format=detailed.pft#1|title=O Meu Pé de Laranja Lima|accessdate=30 April 2014|date=|work=[[Cinemateca Brasileira]]|deadurl=no}}</ref>

== Plot ==
A poor village boy has a single friend —  an orange tree, to whom he trusts his little secrets. But not all trees are destined to live long.
